The Amsterdam Tournament is a pre-season &lt;a href="association%20football"&gt;football&lt;/a&gt; tournament held for club teams from around the world, hosted at the &lt;a href="Amsterdam%20ArenA"&gt;Amsterdam ArenA&lt;/a&gt;. The 2001 tournament was contested by &lt;a href="AFC%20Ajax"&gt;Ajax&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="Liverpool%20F.C."&gt;Liverpool&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="A.C.%20Milan"&gt;Milan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="Valencia%20CF"&gt;Valencia&lt;/a&gt; on 26 July and 28 July 2001. Ajax won the tournament for the first time.
